# Verify live site after changes

**Standing request:** When you make changes that affect the deployed site (e.g. edits to `public/`, or after committing/pushing), check the live site shortly after so updates are showing correctly.

- **Live URL:** https://menu.eatlogicalsentences.com
- **How:** Fetch the URL (e.g. with mcp_web_fetch or equivalent) and confirm the content matches what was changed. Do this as part of your workflow after relevant edits or deploys, not on a schedule — treat it as a default follow-up step.
- If the user just pushed or you just helped push, wait a minute then check. If you only edited files and didn’t push, only check after the user has pushed and had time for Railway to deploy (~1–3 min).
